    {
      "id": "node_1a_woman_at_restaurant",
      "kind": "story",
      "title": "1A. WOMAN AT RESTAURANT",
      "position": {
        "x": 398.6666666666667,
        "y": 902.8333333333333
      },
      "phrases": [
        {
          "id": "phrase_001_heavy_rain_beats_d",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Heavy rain beats down on empty streets as lights from businesses that probably should have closed an hour ago reflect in the shallow pools along the curb. Winter's last chill clings to the spring rain.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_002_in_retrospect_rese",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "In retrospect, reservations at [restaurant] were overkill.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_003_reservations_for_t",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Reservations for two were *definitely* overkill.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_004_that_part_had_been",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "That part had been your ex's idea.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_005_he_wanted_a_second",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "He wanted a second chance. Todd had never been easy to reduce to a villain. He could be thoughtless. Inconsistent. Infuriating in ways that seemed to leave *you* apologizing for being hurt. But he could also look at you like you were the only person in the room, like choosing you was the easiest thing he'd ever done.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_006_that_look_had_been",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "That look had been enough to keep you waiting through a lot.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_007_tonight_it_had_bee",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Tonight it had been enough to get you sitting alone with a half-eaten meal cooling in front of you.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_008_nothing",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "...nothing.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_009_well_nothing_excep",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Well, nothing except a half-empty wine glass, and a plate you can't bring yourself to care about. And some messages from Sammy about her party tomorrow.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_010_the_waiter_approac",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "The waiter approaches, and you realize how late it's gotten.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_011_he_has_gentle_eyes",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "He has gentle eyes and a soft smile. You've tried not to notice- the two of you have been the only people in the restaurant for at least several hours.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_012_ah_i_m_so_sorry_yo",
          "speaker": "Diana",
          "text": "Ah... I'm so sorry. You're probably getting ready to close.\nI promise the food was good. I've just been a little... distracted.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_013_technically_we_clo",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "Technically, we closed about thirty minutes ago.\nYou looked like you were waiting for someone... and like you needed a bit of space.\nBut... if you don't mind...",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_014_you_brace_for_admo",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "You brace for admonishment, or polite pressure, or the familiar embarrassment of being gently moved along. It would be entirely reasonable.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_015_i_m_starting_to_fe",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "...I'm starting to feel a little invested.\nWho are we waiting for?",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_016_my_ex_i_broke_up_w",
          "speaker": "Diana",
          "text": "...my ex.\nI broke up with him a couple months back. One day he'd make me feel like I was his whole world, and the next I'd be checking my phone every fifteen minutes wondering if I'd imagined half our relationship.\nIt looks like he hasn't changed.\n...sorry. I... shouldn't be unloading on you.\nI should go.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_017_the_waiter_waves_o",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "The waiter waves off your concern.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_018_stay_as_long_as_yo",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "Stay as long as you want, ma'am- the storm is getting worse, and I don't have anywhere else to be tonight.\nIt sounds like you're having a rough one- your meal is on the house tonight.\nI can throw in a bit of dessert?",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_019_your_eyebrow_rises",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Your eyebrow rises despite yourself. He notices and fills the silence without missing a beat.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_020_if_the_tiramisu_do",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "If the tiramisu doesn't fix your love life, we do have a backup chocolate cake.\nYou'd be surprised what a good dessert can do.\nLast week I watched a first date play out over our strawberry shortcake. Ended with them going home together. True love, I think. Destined for marriage.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_021_i_don_t_think_i_wa",
          "speaker": "Diana",
          "text": "I don't think I want to reinvent my whole life over dessert.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_022_fair_but_we_all_de",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "Fair- but we all deserve a little treat now and then.\nEspecially on nights like tonight.\nActually... give me one second. I'll be right back.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_023_there_s_an_admirab",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "There's an admirable sort of earnestness to him. You watch as he heads to the kitchen on some sort of mission.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "choice_1a_woman_at_restaurant_1",
              "text": "Leave before dessert",
              "targetNodeId": "node_1b_leave_restaurant_walk_into_rain",
              "conditions": []
            },
            {
              "id": "choice_1a_woman_at_restaurant_2",
              "text": "Stay and flirt",
              "targetNodeId": "node_2b_stay_at_restaurant_flirt",
              "conditions": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "node_1b_leave_restaurant_walk_into_rain",
      "kind": "story",
      "title": "1B. LEAVE RESTAURANT; WALK INTO RAIN",
      "position": {
        "x": 596.9999999999999,
        "y": 900.4999999999999
      },
      "phrases": [
        {
          "id": "phrase_001_left_alone_your_ap",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Left alone, your apprehension rises as quickly as your relief. He seems nice... but a part of you can't help but feel like he's just trying to get into your pants.",
          "effects": [
            {
              "id": "effect_1b_leave_restaurant_walk_into_rain",
              "key": "restaurant_choice",
              "operation": "set",
              "value": "left"
            }
          ],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_002_not_that_that_s_th",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Not that that's the worst thing that could happen.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_003_not_tonight",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Not tonight.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_004_left_alone_at_your",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Left alone at your table, old emotions begin to stew. Todd made you feel that way too, early on. But two years of Todd's excuses, and two years of feeling invisible, bubble up. Something inside you tells you that you need to get out of there. It's almost a panic.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_005_still_nothing_fuck",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Still nothing. Fuck.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_006_the_rain_has_picke",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "The rain has picked up- you're drenched within moments. Your blouse clings to your skin. Water beads on your lashes. The air feels warm with the promise of life, but the rain itself is cold. A shiver runs through you.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_007_todd_s_silence_ton",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Todd's silence tonight probably wasn't malicious, but that almost makes it worse. Malice would've required intention. And this was just more of the same.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_008_there_s_always_a_r",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "There's always a reason. Maybe he got caught in some fresh emergency, some new chaos, some mess dramatic enough that he truly lost track of time and only noticed when it was far too late.\nMaybe he's at home right now, staring at his phone- realizing exactly where the evening went wrong.\nBut it doesn't matter.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_009_your_mind_moves_th",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Your mind moves through all of the versions of tonight you let yourself picture.\nTodd showing up damp from the rain, breathless and apologetic.\nTodd being sincere enough that the rest of the restaurant disappears and it was just you and him.\nTodd finally saying something that closes the distance.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_010_it_feels_stupid_th",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "It feels stupid. There are plenty of people who would've been there for you, but for some reason... that empty chair is all that matters.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_011_rainwater_runs_dow",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "Rainwater runs down the back of your neck.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_012_you_could_keep_wal",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "You could keep walking until the feeling burns off. You can call a ride and get yourself somewhere dry.\nYou could keep telling yourself this is closure. Maybe it'll be true if you say it enough times.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "choice_1b_leave_restaurant_walk_into_rain_1",
              "text": "Keep walking",
              "targetNodeId": "node_3c_continue_walking",
              "conditions": []
            },
            {
              "id": "choice_1b_leave_restaurant_walk_into_rain_2",
              "text": "Call Uber / go back for purse",
              "targetNodeId": "node_1c_go_back_to_restaurant",
              "conditions": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
