      },
      "phrases": [
        {
          "id": "phrase_001_at_some_point_the_",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "At some point the chilled rain stops, leaving only puddles and warm humid air.\nThe pavement almost steams. The whole street feels fuller than it did before, as if the city had quietly decided to start breathing again.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_002_the_car_ride_is_mo",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "The car ride is mostly filled with a warm silence. A part of you knows that if you say anything right now, it will come out as too honest. Too honest about who you are, too honest about what you want.\nThe feeling seems to be mutual.\nThere is a warm apprehension about what comes next. The uncertainty almost feels uplifting.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_003_his_hand_brushes_y",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "His hand brushes yours between the seats before his mouth does- tentative and slow, as if checking if this is what you want.\nHis lips meet yours- warm and careful at first, then sure enough to make heat unfurl low in your body. You lean into the kiss.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_004_if_you_invite_him_",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "If you invite him up, you know what it means. The warmth inside you grows fiery and barely contained. Your skin grows flush... barely containing the escalating hunger.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_005_you_don_t_have_to_",
          "speaker": "Michael",
          "text": "You don't have to decide anything right now.\nI mean it- there's no pressure.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": []
        },
        {
          "id": "phrase_006_he_means_well_but_",
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "text": "He means well, but he's wrong- the pressure wells up inside of you, desperate for release. Desperate to feel him pressed against you.\nYour body has been waiting for this moment.",
          "effects": [],
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "choice_1h_driven_to_her_apartment_1",
              "text": "Say goodnight",
              "targetNodeId": "node_9i_restraint_in_car_say_goodnight",
